702 posted an article titled '5 dumbest things people in their 20s do with money'. This angered many people on Twitter who responded by saying 702 was associating black people with dumbness. After much backlash, 702 removed the post and acknowledged it was insensitive. They tweeted: We apologise for a post on our social media platforms that is offensive. The photograph accompanying an article entitled '5 dumbest things people in their 20s do with money' showed a group of young black people. We acknowledge this was insensitive.Â  It has since been deleted." But twitter users had already made screen grabs of the post.  